cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper focuses on the security and privacy risks associated with IoT devices and proposes a tool for identifying sensitive data flows in IoT applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves software engineering aspects such as static analysis and testing, which makes cs.SE (Software Engineering) another likely category. The tool proposed in the paper involves the translation of IoT source code into an intermediate representation, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also deals with sensitive information, which could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the potential threats to security and privacy, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
